,Recommended,263080,10389293,"Posted: 7 June, 2014",all,C0URAGE,"I have played this game for awhile, and im here to give an honest review. This game is very fun, and addictive, but has some issues, more on that later. Firstly, the game is fun, the ""pixel powers"" are a unique and fresh feature for a rouge-like game. You get powers like bigger bullets, more spread from your shots, and you can even get flaming bullets, and tons more. You can combine the powers to make them even more deadly!! The enemies you encounter are kinda random, you face against ants, frogs, skulls, snakes, slimes, etc. But each have unique attacks. I have gotten to Act 3 now, and the levels never look the same, which is a cool feature. As you would expect in a rouge-like game, once you die you basically lose everything, except the levels, coins, and attributes you gave your character, but i feel like once you die, you should just restart the game, since you lose all the powers you got, and probably dont have enough coins to resupply yourself, but thats to be expected in a game like this. And finally, the bad things/glitches that might happen. The first bad thing, for me, is that the game is short, only 4 acts, and has little replayability, for me of course, but the devs said they are gonna add daily dungeons, so look up on that. The next thing is that the game kinda feels repetitive, other than the Mob Maker 9000 which randomly generates the enemies, you just look for the same three keys, or the RGB, and then you beat the level, and of course, at the end of each act there is a boss, each one i faced was fun and fast paced, really good fights. Those are the bad things, for me, now onto the glitches that you may get, and the ones i experienced. Some enemies or coins will fly off the level, and end up in the blackness, which makes it impossible to get or kill, and the other one is that the enemies will get stuck in the doors, and just wait for you to kill them. Other than that, no more glitches, that i experienced. Overall, this game was very good, i still havent beaten it, but i will. I recommened this game to anyone who like rouge-like games. 8.5/10"
